                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/401: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-24T16:00:00-06:00"
                            >January 24, 1934—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. My telegram No. 4, January 24, 10 a.m. President Carías has informed me that
                    besides sending telegram to Martínez he will tomorrow issue formal decree
                    announcing recognition substance of which I will telegraph Department. Silverio
                    Lainez now confidential agent will be accredited as Honduran Envoy Extraordinary
                    and Minister Plenipotentiary to the present Government of Salvador.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Guatemala and Nicaragua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
